  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to have a cheatcode for getting the current system time in milliseconds since epoch.\r\n\r\nPersonally my main use case is for measuring performance of scripts. Some scripts can become quite complex and I encounter performance issues and I find it useful to measure the time it takes certain parts of the script to run.\r\n\r\nCurrently my solution is to use `vm.ffi(['python', '-c', 'import time; print(int(time.time() * 1000))'])` :sweat_smile: \r\n\r\nThe interface I have in mind is:\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction time () view returns (uint millisecondsSinceEpoch);\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'll also happily open a PR if needed :slightly_smiling_face: \r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
